artifacts.content:
{
  "in_scope": [
    {
      "feature": "Build List Panel",
      "description": "Displays active and completed builds with status indicators, timestamps, and duration",
      "acceptance_criteria": [
        "Displays a list of builds",
        "Each build shows status, timestamp, and duration",
        "Clicking on a build shows build details"
      ],
      "priority": "P0"
    },
    {
      "feature": "Phase Progression Panel",
      "description": "Visual timeline of build phases with status, explanation, and start/end times",
      "acceptance_criteria": [
        "Displays a visual timeline of build phases",
        "Each phase shows status, explanation, and start/end times",
        "Phases are: discovery, design, architecture, frontend, backend, integration, testing, deployment"
      ],
      "priority": "P0"
    },
    {
      "feature": "Agent Roster Panel",
      "description": "List of agents organized by phase with name, role, status, and current task",
      "acceptance_criteria": [
        "Displays a list of agents",
        "Each agent shows name, role, status, and current task",
        "Agents are organized by phase"
      ],
      "priority": "P0"
    },
    {
      "feature": "Constitutional Status Panel",
      "description": "Traffic light system with constitutional checks and status",
      "acceptance_criteria": [
        "Displays a traffic light system",
        "Each check shows article name, status, and explanation",
        "Maximum 7 constitutional checks are displayed"
      ],
      "priority": "P0"
    },
    {
      "feature": "Understanding Your Build Panel",
      "description": "List of generated components/files, key decisions, and known risks",
      "acceptance_criteria": [
        "Displays a list of generated components/files",
        "Key decisions with reasoning are displayed",
        "Known risks with mitigation status are displayed"
      ],
      "priority": "P0"
    },
    {
      "feature": "Contextual Chat Panel",
      "description": "Collapsible side panel for asking questions about the current build",
      "acceptance_criteria": [
        "Panel is collapsible",
        "Panel is only active when a build is selected",
        "Allows asking questions about the current build"
      ],
      "priority": "P1"
    }
  ],
  "out_of_scope": [
    "Mobile optimization",
    "Power-user simplification",
    "Social login (OAuth)",
    "Two-factor authentication",
    "Password reset via SMS",
    "Deploy, download, or override actions"
  ],
  "constraints": [
    "Must use Next.js 14 with App Router",
    "Must use React 18 with Server Components where possible",
    "Must use Tailwind CSS for styling",
    "Must use Lucide React for icons",
    "Must use TypeScript strict mode",
    "Dark theme (slate-900 background) is required",
    "Monospace font for code/data is required",
    "No animations are allowed",
    "No placeholder/mock data is allowed",
    "Traffic light colors: green (#22c55e), yellow (#eab308), red (#ef4444) are required"
  ],
  "assumptions": [
    "Users have modern browsers (Chrome, Firefox, Safari)",
    "Internet connection is required",
    "English language is the default language"
  ],
  "risks": [
    {
      "risk": "Scope creep from stakeholders",
      "mitigation": "Weekly scope review meetings",
      "impact": "high"
    },
    {
      "risk": "Technical debt from using new frameworks",
      "mitigation": "Regular code reviews and testing",
      "impact": "medium"
    }
  ]
}

metadata.name: create_users_table
metadata.sql: CREATE TABLE users (id string PRIMARY KEY, name string, email string, role string)

metadata.name: create_products_table
metadata.sql: CREATE TABLE products (id string PRIMARY KEY, name string, description string, price number, images array, thumbnail_url string, stock_count number, category string)

metadata.name: create_orders_table
metadata.sql: CREATE TABLE orders (id string PRIMARY KEY, user_id string, status string, created_at date, updated_at date, FOREIGN KEY (user_id) REFERENCES users(id))

metadata.name: create_reviews_table
metadata.sql: CREATE TABLE reviews (id string PRIMARY KEY, product_id string, user_id string, rating number, review string, FOREIGN KEY (product_id) REFERENCES products(id), FOREIGN KEY (user_id) REFERENCES users(id))

metadata.name: create_analytics_table
metadata.sql: CREATE TABLE analytics (id string PRIMARY KEY, date date, revenue number, orders number)
